In one encounter with God, everything can change. Regardless of your background or what you are going through, the God of revival and awakening is ready to meet you right where you are at.

We would love for you to join us for our 7th Annual Young Saints Conference [On-Campus and Online] on October 22-23 as we pursue a fresh encounter so that we may once again chase after all that God has in store for us. It is your destiny, as the youth of this generation, to be awakened again and carry power into the world. Speakers will include Ben Fitzgerald, Tom Crandall, and more! Worship from YS Worship.

node.title: Young Saints Conference 2021 - Revival is Now

node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text: “The Lord is my shepherd, I lack nothing. He makes me lie down in green pastures, He leads me beside quiet waters, He refreshes my soul. He guides me along the right paths for His name’s sake. Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me. You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies. You anoint my head with oil; my cup overflows. Surely Your goodness and love will follow me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.” - Psalm 23

node.text:
Have you heard of Young Saints Conference?!
On October 22-23, @bethelyoungsaints is hosting their annual Youth Conference and we couldn't be more excited about it. You can experience the revival either In-person or online. Speakers include @bendavidfitzgerald @havilahcunnington & @tom_crandall
God is moving in the youth and we are expectant for what the future holds!

Also, for youth pastors & youth groups -  if you register by TODAY, you will enter into a fun giveaway for your youth group! 

Register now at bethel.com/events

node.text: We’re excited for the fresh vision and hope that will be given to you at Open Heavens, happening September 29-October 1. This year, we've gathered a powerful group of leaders to speak, including guest speaker Chad Veach of ZOE Church LA, and Bethel leaders Bill Johnson, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Jenn Johnson, and more! We believe that each of these speakers is carrying something uniquely important for this season, something that will refresh, revive, and rekindle the Body of Christ to their calling of showing the world who Jesus is. Join us! #OpenHeavens2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on September 11, 2021. May be a black-and-white image.

node.text: Today, we reflect on what happened 20 years ago in our nation. We came together to grieve and believe our future was secure and filled with promise. We believe the same for this day. God, we pray that You would unite us and bring Your promises of healing to our land.

node.text: On Sunday, August 8, we broke ground on our new Collyer Campus! We’re so grateful for those who were able to join, and those who have helped this day to arrive, and we have great hope for all that’s ahead!
